			forms by which P may question R on any matter which is or may be relevant;
			forms by which R may answer questions by P.
		A question by P or an answer by R is admissible as evidence in proceedingsunder this Act (whether or not the question or answer is contained in aprescribed form).
		A court or tribunal may draw an inference from—
			a failure by R to answer a question by P before the end of the period of 8weeks beginning with the day on which the question is served;
			an evasive or equivocal answer.
		Subsection (4) does not apply if—
			R reasonably asserts that to have answered differently or at all might haveprejudiced a criminal matter;
			R reasonably asserts that to have answered differently or at all would haverevealed the reason for not commencing or not continuing criminal proceedings;
